headline: Laura Ingraham Imitates Kate McKinnon's Impression Of Her And Reviews Pour In
author: Ron Dicker
sentences:
Ingraham does an impression of Kate McKinnon doing an impression of her pic.twitter.com/MRomgXVulU
— Acyn (@Acyn) January 25, 2022
“I like doing Kate McKinnon doing me, ’cause she’s kinda fun,” Ingraham said.
Laura Ingraham on Monday broke out her impression of Kate McKinnon imitating her on “Saturday Night Live” over the weekend - and the Fox News host didn’t make a very good impression.
She noted the “low-hanging fruit provided by Joe Biden and Nancy Pelosi” in her routine, and offered to go on “SNL” and impersonate the House speaker for free.
Mike Huckabee, a guest on “The Ingraham Angle,” said it was up to the likes of Ingraham to show that conservatives have a sense of humor.
